tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mild hypoglycemia, elevated serum creatinine suggesting possible renal impairment, and significant proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria. Urine is brown, cloudy, and has low specific gravity, but no hematuria or leukocyturia. These findings may indicate impaired renal function, possible diabetic ketoacidosis, or other metabolic disturbances. Clinical correlation and further evaluation are recommended.
